			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing tactics that still work?<a name="65578"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 4 04 2:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Did I miss something?  He asked for viable solo tactics, it is in the subject as well....so how can this not be about soloing ?
<br />

<br />
Pre 50 with no area kites.  Mele is the fastest way to reach 50, now this is somewhat gear dependant sure, but chanting one at a time is slow, fear kiting is slow solo, charm kiting is a disturbance pre 50 in zones full of the newbies or alts grinding, but even charm kiting is not much faster pre 50.
<br />

<br />
Grouping is the easy part of being a Bard I have always found.  Soloing is where you skill up and learn the songs.  You just sing them to yourself.  Grouping is going to get you social interaction, but not fast leveling.  There is plenty of time to charm in your 50's..you can learn it in 5 minutes.
<br />

<br />
The power of damage shield, dot, instrument switching, maxing skills, mezzing, charming 1 pet to use for extra mele damge along side you, fearing, regening, lulling, snaring, slowing, what ever else I missed is going to get your skils up and ready for grouping.  You can learn to pull in 5 minutes, then you need practice...well you can practice solo pulling a lot better than looking stupid learning it grouped.  To pull singles is pretty necesary if you are inside a dungeon and solo....
<br />

<br />
To each his own, for sure.  I did do 0 to 50 in 5 days played solo...no powerlevel, no groups, no kiting...all mele.  To save or spend a few extra days would be meaningless. It would still be fast enough.
<br />

<br />
Trust me, by 50 I knew the songs inside out, had massive knowledge about pulling singles, aggro ranges, lulling, pet actions (this is how the nerf to our dots was so apparent, as Sony changed it about 4 times back and forth).
<br />

<br />
95% of what you learn grouped, you also learn solo....as long as you are not kiting.  If it is you and 1 mob, or you and a pet and 1 mob...it is the same nearly.
<br />

<br />
The 5% extra is easy to come by.  Being grouped at 50 with the deffensive ability of a lv20 is going to have you regretting it.
<br />

<br />
Oh, the kite part...well even though the pre 50 was all mele for me...I was the MASTER of kiting and still am to this day.  (that is how easy it was)  Area kiting at lv 65 was sweet yes, but it is gone.
<br />

<br />
Charm Kiting is easy, but can be fun when done indoors with no place to run.  That is aggro management at its best.  LDON will be great for grouping later.
<br />

<br />
You probably want 2 things to hapen...get out of lv 30 and reach 65 fairly quick, and 2 be a skilled and wanted member of the bard comunity so people ask you to join them once you get there.  Looking dumb is nice to do alone, and eventually you are 65 and will group almost all the time since we pretty much suck solo after 65 compared to grouped.
<br />

<br />
As an aside...what is better than calling yourself a decent bard?   Your guild calling you a decent Bard?  Even better a Guild other than your own calling you a good Bard, and finally other Bards calling you a good Bard.
<br />

<br />
If you play to be good, you will be....but you gotta start someplace.
<br />

<br />
Moose   </span></td>
