				<td colspan="2"><span>In my 30's I melee'd for the most part.  I fought a lot in Echo Caverns for example, the Needlites there are good exp up to 32 and  not terrible up to 36.  Use whatever damage shield options you have, a psalm and a Singing Steel Bracer will help quite a bit.  I learned to kite on the Zelniaks and wolves and such in DSP over by the entrance to Sanctus Seru, this is a nice zone because it's easy to solo and to find groups.  I did all my levelling though before LoY came out.  Gunthak and Dulak's are great for both kiting and melee soloing as well as grouping.  Again, heavy on the Damage Shield pullundead so they don't run and keep bangning away on your DS till the very end and the loot isn't bad for the levels.
<br />

<br />
You do want to melee quite a bit, you'll learn the songs better and you'll keep your skills up, only way to get Defense up is to get hit after all.  Charm kiting is fun and spent a lot of time charming giants in EW and BW, good loot, spell drops and reasonable exp.  The big recent nerf was to AE Kiting, something I never did till i was 65 and wanted to knock out some quick AA's.  got to 65 and 200+ AA before I ever tried AE kiting, about equal parts solo/grouping.</span></td>
