				<td colspan="2"><span>Moose,
<br />
You had several valid points but this...
<br />

<br />
&quot;Pre 50 with no area kites. Mele is the fastest way to reach 50, now this is somewhat gear dependant sure, but chanting one at a time is slow, fear kiting is slow solo, charm kiting is a disturbance pre 50 in zones full of the newbies or alts grinding, but even charm kiting is not much faster pre 50. &quot;
<br />

<br />
...is just wrong.
<br />

<br />
The only added damage melee has over a fear kite is damage shield.  This is offset by the damage the bard takes himself.  How is it fear kite is slow but melee is fast?
<br />

<br />
Yes chant kiting is slow, but with fantastic weapons and a good drum, a bard does more damage with the drum and 3 chants.  Add groupmates to haste and that picture changes.
<br />

<br />
Charm kiting is a disturbance?  What?  How is taking 2 mobs at once a disturbance?  Perhaps you meant swarm kiting but I would still disagree if the bard is considerate.  And 2 mobs PLUS my chants has always outdone my melee output (get credit for the damage each mob does.  If by this you meant swarm kiting  and said &quot;it's not that much faster&quot;, you do NOT know how to swarm.  
<br />

<br />
In swarm kiting with others in the zone, I have generally killed faster than full groups.  A rate of a kill a minute means I'm coasting or screwing up.  I have PLed people close to my level who got faster xps sitting on a hillside afk leaching off me than they would in a group.  If groups are sharing the zone I will find an out of the way spot, from 27-65 there are places to choose.  
<br />

<br />
In short, for speed of leveling, swarming blows all others (except well done AOE) away.  Uber-twinked melee doesn't even come close.
<br />

<br />
Like I said though, your approach has some merits.  Certainly your way, melee skills would be MUCH healthier thru the whole curve.  Certainly my defense lagged behind in the 40s because I blew thru those levels swarming about half the time (grouping the rest).  But LDON fixed all that for me... pull... thwap thwap...skill up...pull... </span></td>
