				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing tactics that still work?<a name="65690"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 5 04 2:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Donvanlot,
<br />
In response to this:
<br />
&quot;also have to question well done AE. Almost any AE was better than swarming for exp. Nadox exp at at 60s was insane.&quot;
<br />

<br />
Maybe you don't give yourself enough credit.  Or maybe you ignore the downsides.
<br />

<br />
If I am swarming hobgoblins / wraiths while you are AEing Nadox... And we are both doing it for an hour... and you die twice, spending 15 minutes of that hour doing CRs, regathering your kite and looking for rezzes... I win.  During those 15 iminutes I am gaining on you the whole time
<br />

<br />
If you dont die.. you win, hands down, unless you have a lot of trouble getting your AE to stick because you are too far away a lot of the time.
<br />

<br />
Survival was the biggest differentiator between good AE kiting, mediocre AE kiting and bad AE kiting.  Not from the xp lose after the rez.. from the XP loss of not kiting while you CR.
<br />

<br />
If you died a lot AE kiting sucked.  Lots of people who tried it died a lot.  Maybe you were better at it than you credit yourself.</span></td>
